Although Tajikistan, like other countries of the region, followed the model of the Western colonialism, what distinguished the process in Tajikistan, was that the Western colonial agents allocated their proxy army to go East to attack the destination country. So we see Russia, who took revenge on all countries of East Asia for all past ‘insults’ against them, going into the Soviet Union and India. Even America, in the aftermath of the Second World War, had a hubristic idealism to build its name upon. This was achieved by allowing and supporting Britain to build the Suez Canal, Sudan being British, and Egypt, Turkish Ataturk, a fellow colonial, would not destroy her Vassal state. That did not happen soon afterwards, the Commonwealth formed by Saad ben Lebbe refused such matters, India will not be allowed to pass through Pakistan to get to Afghanistan. India on her disdainful basis against the US, romance with USSR and the West, rejected this alliance. India stressed that it is our country that we will go to fight and not sit behind the Western troops to fight the final war. Pakistan retaliated to the Indian refusal and sent the Mujahideen into Afghanistan. Pakistan money was more important than joint cooperation.
